The paper deals with communication systems and channel estimation, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of codes to guarantee reliable communication suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY), while the investigation of feedback for quantized CSI points towards networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the comparison of EIO rates with a mismatched ML decoder involves statistical signal processing (cs.MM).
